river.</li>\n<li><strong>Target 16.5</strong> <em>(Reduce Corruption):</em></li>\n<li>The feeling of something being “sticky” or difficult to move.</li>\n<li>The image of a spiderweb trapping something.</li>\n<li><strong>Target 16.6</strong> <em>(Accountable Institutions):</em></li>\n<li>The image of many hands working together to build something.</li>\n<li>The feeling of a building with strong foundations.</li>\n<li><strong>Target 16.7</strong> <em>(Inclusive Decision Making):</em></li>\n<li>The action of many people contributing to a central point.</li>\n<li>A circle of people all facing inwards.</li>\n<li><strong>Target 16.8</strong> <em>(Global Governance):</em></li>\n<li>The image of different shapes fitting together.</li>\n<li>Different musical instruments playing together.</li>\n<li><strong>Target 16.9</strong> <em>(Legal Identity):</em></li>\n<li>The action of someone being recognized or seen clearly.</li>\n<li>A single fingerprint.</li>\n<li><strong>Target 16.10</strong> <em>(Access to Information):</em></li>\n<li>The gesture of opening or revealing something.</li>\n<li>A beam of light cutting through darkness.</li>\n<li><strong>Target 16.a</strong> <em>(Strengthen Institutions):</em></li>\n<li>The feeling of providing support or reinforcement.</li>\n<li>The action of tying a knot to make something stronger</li>\n<li><strong>Target 16.b</strong> <em>(Non-Discrimination):</em></li>\n<li>The action of separating and then coming together equally.</li>\n<li>Different colors blending together.</li>\n</ul><br>Begin guided improvisation and vocal/movement building by guiding the class through a series of simple, whole-class improvisations based on the brainstormed ideas for each stimulus, encouraging both vocal and movement improvisation.<br>For each target/idea, lead a short (2-3 minute) exploration:<br>Examples:\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Target 16.1</strong> <em>(Reduce Violence):</em></li>\n<li>Let’s explore the feeling of a tightly clenched fist slowly opening. Every